Preparatory committee in Guyana 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- A preparatory committee for celebration of the 59th birthday of leader Kim Jong Il was formed in Guyana.
 The Minister of Public Service of Guyana said in an inaugural meeting held in Georgetown on Jan. 5 that it has become the trend of the times to significantly celebrate Kim Jong Il's birthday worldwide. He highly praised the feats performed by him on behalf of the Korean people and the world people.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting the minister of public service and the Minister of Amerindian Affairs of Guyana were elected co-chairmen of the preparatory committee, the leader of the good green Guyana first vice-chairman of the committee and the chairman of the Guyana-Korea Friendship Association general secretary of the committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee set the period from Jan. 5 to Feb. 28 as a period of celebrations and decided to hold multifarious political and cultural events. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its participants called upon governments, political parties and public organizations of various countries to commemorate next year the 90th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung and the birthday of Kim Jong Il as a grand political festival worldwide.

Japan urged to own responsibility for its past crimes 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun today carries an article of Dr. Jong Nam Yong who participated in the "Women's International War Crimes Tribunal on Japan's Military Sexual Slavery" in Tokyo from December 8 to 12, 2000.
 The tribunal was participated in by at least 1,000 persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 among them were prosecutors groups of nine countries and regions of Asia that fell victim to those crimes and former "Comfort Women for the Army" including the prosecutors group of the "DPRK measure committee for demanding compensation to comfort women for the army and the victims of the Pacific War" and former "Comfort Women for the Army" from the north and the south of Korea, women victims of sexual abuses committed in different countries at present, ex-soldiers of the imperial Japanese army, judges, international prosecutors group, prosecutors, lawyers, famous jurists and human rights experts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tribunal heard indictments made by prosecutors from different countries on the crimes related to Japan's military sexual slavery and testimonies of former "Comfort Women for the Army" and ex-soldiers of the imperial Japanese army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lawyers of the Japanese side pleaded and the international prosecutors group made addresses at the tribunal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tribunal prosecuted and tried Japanese emperor Hirohito who was not prosecuted at the Tokyo international tribunal in 1946, and convicted him of the crimes. It taught a serious historical lesson that though those involved in the most hideous crimes related to sexual slavery could escape from a legal punishment temporarily by playing a sleight of hand, they are bound to face a fair judgement by humankind even after their deaths unless they are settled. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The tribunal ruled that the Japanese government should make a state apology and compensation for its crimes. This once again proved the truth that the unethical crimes committed against other countries and nations can never be concealed no matter how much water flows under the bridge and how many generations are replaced and they are bound to be settled through generations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The north and south Korean prosecutors groups worked out and published a joint indictment in which they clarified the social and historical background against which crimes related to "Comfort Women for the Army" were committed by the former Japanese government and army against Korean women, evidence enough to declare the former Japanese government and military bosses including emperor Hirohito guilty, important information and a legal ground to force the present Japanese government to own state responsibility and issues to be solved by it to fulfil its responsibility. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article strongly urged the Japanese authorities not to forget the lesson of history or depart from requirements and truth of the international law but face up to the trend of the times and make an apology and compensation for the crimes committed against the Korean people, sincerely repentant of them.

Rodong Sinmun on WPK's all-embracing politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il's patriotic all-embracing politics provides a sure guarantee for accomplishing the cause of great national unity, the cause of national reunification, says Rodong Sinmun today in a signed article.
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prosperity of the Korean nation and its reunification can be achieved only when Kim Jong Il's politics of noble humanity, the most generous patriotic politics is upheld. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His is the politics of love and trust and all-embracing politics. His all-embracing politics represents the politics of warmest human love and the most generous patriotic politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il wisely leads the whole nation to achieve the great unity for national reunification, the cause common to the nation, anchored on patriotism and national identity irrespective of ideology, system, political view, religious belief, given that there exist different classes and social circles within our nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The politics calls for uniting with all those desirous of national reunification with national conscience and working together in the one and same ranks for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This politics invites even those who once took a wrong road to turn to patriotism, repentant of their wrongs, calls for leniently treating those who went amiss, betraying the nation in the past, on the principle of not caring about their past, and lets them join the movement for national reunification if they, sincerely remorseful of their wrong doings, are willing to contribute to the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il clarified his stand to unite under the banner of the great national unity with even the authorities, ruling and opposition party figures, big capitalists and army generals of South Korea if they value the common interests of the nation and desire the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's all-embracing politics is, indeed, the politics of noble love and the most generous patriotic politics which embraces all those desirous of reunification with national conscience and leads them to reunification and patriotism.

New teeth correction device developed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, January 10 (KCNA) -- Dental surgeons at the dental hospital under the Ministry of Public Health have recently developed a teeth correction device and a dental deodorant.
 The new device is simple to handle compared with the old ones. It is so fixed to the teeth during the correction that it does not bother the users, producing better results. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has the high correction rate, reduces the correction period by two thirds and has no aftereffects. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A dental deodorant manufactured by Ra Mi Un now wins popularity. A pill is put into the mouth and it begins to show efficacy in minutes. It lasts more than four hours. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; It has no side effects. Its main ingredient is so locally available that it can be made by other dental centres.
